data.text:
Profession: Singer

Biography: Robbie Williams began his career as a member of the British boy band Take That, but found even greater commercial success as a solo artist.

Williams was 16 years old when he joined Take That in 1989 and stayed until 1995. Williams went on to rejoin the band 2010-2014.

Williams has sold more than 77 million albums and singles worldwide, and is the best-selling British solo artist in the United Kingdom and the best selling non-Latino artist in Latin America.

Born: February 13, 1974

Birthplace: Stoke-on-Trent, England

Age: 50 years old
